Paolo Privitera, CEO Evensi

Paolo, MIT MBA 2021, is currently the CEO and co-founder of Evensi, the world's largest events discovery and promotion network, with more than 200 million events, 50 million users, 10 million event organizers. The company has been approved for an IPO.

Paolo is a Silicon Valley-based global entrepreneur and strategist with a passion for innovation and growth using the power of data, strategic analysis, creativity, and teamwork.
Born and raised in Venice Italy, he founded his first Internet company in 1994 when he was 16 years old.

host_about: Hi there! Welcome! I'm a friendly and gracious hostess that loves meeting new people.  With over 250 glowing reviews and 11 years of hosting (yikes!) you can't go wrong.  I have been in Los Angeles for 34 years, originally from DC, definitely an East-coast girl only in better weather.  I'm a living, breathing YELP/TripAdvisor, knowing a good deal of the area's restaurants (the ones where the locals go), our great music venues, museums, as well as, nearby hiking trails and beaches.   Also, somewhat of a savant when it comes to the best routes to take during rush hour. I beat Waze by 10 minutes going downtown just today. I'll go head-to-head with your GPS apps anytime.  I love my dogs, cooking, gardening, interior design and traveling.  Come by.  Stay a while!  Share my homey space.

Mid-City is a neighborhood in Central Los Angeles, California near Culver City & Miracle Mile. It's smack dab in the center of Los Angeles hence the name.

Attractions include La Brea Tar Pits & Museum, the Insta-famous "Urban Light" installation by Chris Burden, restaurants and a post office named for singer Ray Charles, who had his recording studio in Mid-City. The neighborhood hosts eleven public and private schools.

The city's hub: Almost anywhere you work in L.A., you're a relatively short drive away (except the Valley — sorry!). There also are two Expo Line stations with parking lots nearby for those who are looking for an easier commute.
A diner's delight: Chicken and waffles at Roscoe's. Injera and doro wot in Little Ethiopia. Proximity to Pico Boulevard, one of L.A.'s best streets for foodies.

“Parties or events not allowed”

neighborhood_overview: The Enchanted Manor is on a quiet tree lined cut de sac. Behind the house is the LA River so there are no houses there. It's a private and serine space for your enjoyment. Grocery stores and restaurants are within walking distance.
host_about:
I am a Stunt Driver and the author of "The Company She Keeps" my autobiography which ha recently been optioned for a movie. I purchased my property in 1983 and it has been an ongoing labor of love every since. Over the years I have put in over a million dollars, creating a magical paradise. The original size of the home was 2800 sq.ft. It is now 5000 sq. ft. I am 58 years old and have recently adopted a baby. I have elected to stay at home and be a mom. Renting my property is a way of making an income which allows me to be at home rather than on location. I have built a play house and tree house on the property (inspired by my daughter) which is a real plus for renter's with young children. The play house is a mini version of the main house with a river rock exterior, bay windows, skylights, custom made child size leather couch, bunk beds, cable TV, phone line, fireplace and camera system to monitor the children from inside the house. It has it's own patio with a child size umbrella table. It truly is a child's wonderland.

People come to The Enchanted Manor as strangers and leave as friends. I live on the property, but your privacy is respected. I am available 24hours a day to help to make your stay an enjoyable adventure.

neighborhood_overview: We are very central to so many tourist destinations like LAX, Hollywood, Universal city, Santa Monica pier, 40 mins to Malibu and only an hour’s drive from Disneyland!
host_about:
...Pronouced like a car with and ee at the end. I am a people person and love the outdoors. We love having visitors in our guesthouse! It not only gives them a lovely place of well-being in busy Los Angeles, but it also allows our family to connect with adults and kids from around the world. My profile photo is taken in the Flathead Indian territory  in Northern Montana while photographing my family in the mountains.
 My background is in the visual arts with a long work history in the film business. I love documenting the world around me through photos and video. In recent years, i've spent most of my time raising our twins, gardening and finding breaks for yoga & swimming, shooting promo videos and concert events and helping a group of founding parents start a public Spanish immersion elementary school in the West Adams area of Los Angeles.

Our family loves to travel, cook, swim, hike, eat healthily, and attend the free summer/fall musical outdoor jazz & Latin jazz family picnic concerts in the nearby LAcMA park on Friday and Saturday evenings. For many years we've had an eclectic mix of guests renting our charming guesthouse primarily through word of mouth. In the last four years, we've expanded our network and are SO excited to have met a wonderful new group of guests via  Airbnb. We ve had an AMAZING group of visitors and return guests to whom we are very grateful!!!....and hope to see again and again.

As a host, I pride myself on helping guests in any way I can....whether it be providing an iron/ironing board for a wedding, or special baby gear, referring a special restaurant in the area or across town, giving directions to my favorite semi-private Malibu & Santa Barbara beaches, or helping a family enroll their kids in the nearby museum s NExtGen Sunday free art program....I am here to help...Please ask! 

I speak fluent French and am getting myself and our family up to speed on Spanish. Our small guesthouse library has books on many subjects in English (and some in French & Spanish). In addition to the guesthouse space, we encourage our guests to use the outdoor backyard shared spaces (shown in our photos) if they have time and just want to hang out and read and recline with the birds and our sometimes friendly and sometimes shy cat Samson.
